replies.body:
{{champion:91}} {{champion:238}} 

Both healing assassins.  Just because they don't have it innately built in doesn't mean they don't benefit monstrously from lifesteal and Elixir of Wrath.

You're pointing out one simple thing on Ekko that honestly, if you'd take like 5 seconds to consider it, hardly offers up as much of a problem as you make it out to be.  His trail is traceable, he's pretty easy to locate, he's fucked without his ult, and his entire kit relies on being able to either move or use his abilities.  Stop letting him engage on you and charge his ass when he whiffs his W - his burst is only exceptional if he's ahead.  Most assassins already in the game pack far more upfront power than he could dream of unless he actually manages to nail his ult on a squishy target, which there's not only a clone of him indicating where it'll land - it's marked by a big fuckin' red arrow saying, "HEY, HEY. THIS SPOT HERE? DON'T FUCKING STAND HERE."  His W is otherwise the only major reason teamfights can be tipped decisively in his favor, and that takes 3 goddamn seconds to warm-up and drop in the designated area, _and_ you get a .5 second warning on it as well, which is more of a warning than most champs give you other than, "Hey my high CC high damage ult's up k you're dead now bai nao~."
